!! Visual Representation of the Editing Workflow

The following diagram illustrates the complete flow from user editing to changes going live.

!!! User Perspective

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 1. USER VISITS WIKI                                         │
│    https://anicolao.github.io/practical-copilot-wiki/       │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 2. USER MAKES EDITS                                         │
│    • Click edit button on existing tiddlers                 │
│    • Create new tiddlers                                    │
│    • Delete unwanted tiddlers                               │
│    • Preview changes locally in browser                     │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 3. USER SUBMITS CHANGES                                     │
│    • Click "Submit Changes" button                          │
│    • Review captured changes                                │
│    • System opens GitHub issue form                         │
│    • Changes are pre-filled in issue body                   │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 4. USER COMPLETES ISSUE                                     │
│    • Add description of changes (summary)                   │
│    • Add any additional context                             │
│    • Check the checklist boxes                              │
│    • Submit the GitHub issue                                │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 5. WAIT FOR REVIEW                                          │
│    • Issue is labeled "wiki-edit, needs-review"             │
│    • User receives GitHub notifications                     │
│    • Can respond to maintainer questions                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

!!! Maintainer Perspective

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 1. MAINTAINER RECEIVES NOTIFICATION                         │
│    • GitHub notifies of new wiki-edit issue                 │
│    • Review issue content and changes                       │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 2. MAINTAINER CREATES BRANCH                                │
│    • Create branch: feature/wiki-edit-{issue-number}        │
│    • Apply changes from issue to tiddler files              │
│    • Commit changes to branch                               │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 3. MAINTAINER OPENS PULL REQUEST                            │
│    • Create PR from feature branch to main                  │
│    • Link to original issue                                 │
│    • PR triggers preview deployment workflow                │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 4. PREVIEW DEPLOYMENT                                       │
│    • GitHub Actions builds wiki with changes                │
│    • Deploys to pr-{number} subdirectory on gh-pages        │
│    • Bot comments on PR with preview URL                    │
│    • Example: .../practical-copilot-wiki/pr-42/             │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 5. REVIEW AND MERGE                                         │
│    • Maintainer reviews changes in preview                  │
│    • Checks for formatting, accuracy, quality               │
│    • Merges PR if approved                                  │
│    • Closes original issue                                  │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 6. AUTOMATIC DEPLOYMENT                                     │
│    • Merge to main triggers deploy workflow                 │
│    • Wiki is rebuilt with new changes                       │
│    • Deployed to main GitHub Pages site                     │
│    • Changes are live within minutes                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

