!! Key Components

* ''TiddlyWiki Instance'': Single-page application loaded in user's browser
* ''GitHub Saver Plugin'': Custom TiddlyWiki plugin that replaces save mechanism
* ''Issue Template'': Standardized format for wiki edit submissions
* ''GitHub Actions'': Automated build and deployment workflows
* ''GitHub Pages'': Hosting platform for main wiki and PR previews

!! Data Flow

# User edits happen entirely in browser memory
# On "submit", changes are serialized to text format
# GitHub issue URL is constructed with changes in query parameters
# User completes issue submission on GitHub
# Maintainer manually applies changes to tiddler files
# Pull request triggers automated preview deployment
# Merge to main triggers production deployment
